                                        STATIC IMPORT
                                        =============



---> This is  a normal program for import---->
---> Drawback is , if we have 100 methods in Person, we have to write one by one using classname, to minimize the boiler plate code, we choose static import.
- -> Static import is used to access static members directly without using class name.

Person.java
===========

package com.ibm.aadhar;

public class Person {
	
	public static void speak() {
		
		System.out.println("Hi, I am Rajat");
	}
	
public static void m1() {
		
		System.out.println("Hi, I am m1() method");
	}

public static void m2() {
	
	System.out.println("Hi, I am m2() method");
}

}


