                                        VARIABLE ARGUMENTS (var args)
                                        ==============================
--> introduced in java 1.5
--> when we don't know how many parameters to take for a method then we can use var-args.
--> Variable argument should be the last argument of the method.
--> A method should contain only one variable argument.

                                    Syntax:  public int add(int... x){
                                    
                                    
                                    }

NOTE: (int... x) ---> these dots are called ellipses--> only 3 ellipse are allowed to declare variable argument.

public void m1(String s, int... a)//valid
public void m1(String s, boolean... b)//valid
public void m1(int a, String... s)//valid
public void m1(int... a)//valid
public void m1(double.... d)//Invalid
public void m1(int... a, int b)//Invalid
public void m1(int i, int... j)//valid


one example for normal method overloading
